events.description: King Richard I of England is wounded by a crossbow bolt while fighting in France, leading to his death on April 6.
events.html: • 1199 – King Richard I of England is wounded by a crossbow bolt while fighting in France, leading to his death on April 6.[1][2][3]

events.description: English victory over a Franco-Castilian-Flemish fleet in the Battle of Margate off the coast of Margate.
events.html: • 1387 – English victory over a Franco-Castilian-Flemish fleet in the Battle of Margate off the coast of Margate.[4]

events.description: Turco-Mongol emperor Timur sacks Damascus.
events.html: • 1401 – Turco-Mongol emperor Timur sacks Damascus.[5][6]

events.description: James VI of Scotland is proclaimed King James I of England and Ireland, upon the death of Elizabeth I.
events.html: • 1603 – James VI of Scotland is proclaimed King James I of England and Ireland, upon the death of Elizabeth I.[7]

events.description: Tokugawa Ieyasu is granted the title of shōgun from Emperor Go-Yōzei, and establishes the Tokugawa shogunate in Edo, Japan.
events.html: • 1603 – Tokugawa Ieyasu is granted the title of shōgun from Emperor Go-Yōzei, and establishes the Tokugawa shogunate in Edo, Japan.[8][9]

events.description: The Province of Carolina is granted by charter to eight Lords Proprietor in reward for their assistance in restoring Charles II of England to the throne.
events.html: • 1663 – The Province of Carolina is granted by charter to eight Lords Proprietor in reward for their assistance in restoring Charles II of England to the throne.[10][11]

events.description: Count Frederick of Hesse-Kassel is elected King of Sweden by the Riksdag of the Estates, after his consort Ulrika Eleonora abdicated the throne on 29 February.
events.html: • 1720 – Count Frederick of Hesse-Kassel is elected King of Sweden by the Riksdag of the Estates, after his consort Ulrika Eleonora abdicated the throne on 29 February.[12][13]

events.description: Johann Sebastian Bach dedicated six concertos to Margrave Christian Ludwig of Brandenburg-Schwedt, now commonly called the Brandenburg Concertos, BWV 1046–1051.
events.html: • 1721 – Johann Sebastian Bach dedicated six concertos to Margrave Christian Ludwig of Brandenburg-Schwedt, now commonly called the Brandenburg Concertos, BWV 1046–1051.[14][15]

events.description: Great Britain passes the Quartering Act, which requires the Thirteen Colonies to house British troops.
events.html: • 1765 – Great Britain passes the Quartering Act, which requires the Thirteen Colonies to house British troops.[16][17]

entities.name: British Army during the American Revolutionary War

events.description: In Kraków, Tadeusz Kościuszko announces a general uprising against Imperial Russia and the Kingdom of Prussia, and assumes the powers of the Commander in Chief of all of the Polish forces.
events.html: • 1794 – In Kraków, Tadeusz Kościuszko announces a general uprising against Imperial Russia and the Kingdom of Prussia, and assumes the powers of the Commander in Chief of all of the Polish forces.[18][19][20]

events.description: The Parliament of the United Kingdom passes the Roman Catholic Relief Act 1829, allowing Catholics to serve in Parliament.
events.html: • 1829 – The Parliament of the United Kingdom passes the Roman Catholic Relief Act 1829, allowing Catholics to serve in Parliament.[21][22]

events.description: In Hiram, Ohio, a group of men beat and tar and feather Mormon leader Joseph Smith.
events.html: • 1832 – In Hiram, Ohio, a group of men beat and tar and feather Mormon leader Joseph Smith.[23][24]

events.description: President José Gregorio Monagas abolishes slavery in Venezuela.
events.html: • 1854 – President José Gregorio Monagas abolishes slavery in Venezuela.[25][26]

events.description: Sakuradamon Incident: Japanese Chief Minister (Tairō) Ii Naosuke is assassinated by rōnin samurai outside the Sakurada Gate of Edo Castle.
events.html: • 1860 – Sakuradamon Incident: Japanese Chief Minister (Tairō) Ii Naosuke is assassinated by rōnin samurai outside the Sakurada Gate of Edo Castle.[27]

events.description: The last of Tītokowaru's forces surrendered to the New Zealand government, ending his uprising.
events.html: • 1869 – The last of Tītokowaru's forces surrendered to the New Zealand government, ending his uprising.[28]

events.description: A Chilean prospecting party led by José Díaz Gana discovers the silver ores of Caracoles in the Bolivian portion of Atacama Desert,  leading to the last of the Chilean silver rushes  and a diplomatic dispute over its taxation between Chile and Bolivia.
events.html: • 1870 – A Chilean prospecting party led by José Díaz Gana discovers the silver ores of Caracoles in the Bolivian portion of Atacama Desert,[29] leading to the last of the Chilean silver rushes[30] and a diplomatic dispute over its taxation between Chile and Bolivia.[31][32]

events.description: The British frigate HMS Eurydice sinks, killing more than 300.
events.html: • 1878 – The British frigate HMS Eurydice sinks, killing more than 300.[33][34][35]

events.description: Robert Koch announces the discovery of Mycobacterium tuberculosis, the bacterium responsible for tuberculosis.
events.html: • 1882 – Robert Koch announces the discovery of Mycobacterium tuberculosis, the bacterium responsible for tuberculosis.[36][37]

events.description: Mayor of New York City Robert Anderson Van Wyck breaks ground for a new underground "Rapid Transit Railroad" that would link Manhattan and Brooklyn.
events.html: • 1900 – Mayor of New York City Robert Anderson Van Wyck breaks ground for a new underground "Rapid Transit Railroad" that would link Manhattan and Brooklyn.[38][39][40]

events.description: Carnegie Steel Company is formed in New Jersey; its capitalization of $160 million is the largest to date.
events.html: • 1900 – Carnegie Steel Company is formed in New Jersey; its capitalization of $160 million is the largest to date.[41]

events.description: The 1921 Women's Olympiad began in Monte Carlo, becoming the first international women's sports event.
events.html: • 1921 – The 1921 Women's Olympiad began in Monte Carlo, becoming the first international women's sports event.[42][43]

events.description: The McMahon killings take place in Belfast. Six Catholic civilians are shot dead, two others wounded and a female family member assaulted. Police were suspected as being responsible, but no one was prosecuted.
events.html: • 1922 – The McMahon killings take place in Belfast. Six Catholic civilians are shot dead, two others wounded and a female family member assaulted. Police were suspected as being responsible, but no one was prosecuted.[44]

events.description: Nanking Incident: Foreign warships bombard Nanjing, China, in defence of the foreign citizens within the city.
events.html: • 1927 – Nanking Incident: Foreign warships bombard Nanjing, China, in defence of the foreign citizens within the city.[45][46]

events.description: The Tydings–McDuffie Act is passed by the United States Congress, allowing the Philippines to become a self-governing commonwealth.
events.html: • 1934 – The Tydings–McDuffie Act is passed by the United States Congress, allowing the Philippines to become a self-governing commonwealth.[47][48]

events.description: The 1939 Liechtenstein putsch takes place; approximately 40 members of the VBDL starting from Nendeln march towards Vaduz with the intention of overthrowing the government and provoking Liechtenstein's annexation into Germany.
events.html: • 1939 – The 1939 Liechtenstein putsch takes place; approximately 40 members of the VBDL starting from Nendeln march towards Vaduz with the intention of overthrowing the government and provoking Liechtenstein's annexation into Germany.[49]

events.description: German troops massacre 335 Italian civilians in Rome.
events.html: • 1944 – German troops massacre 335 Italian civilians in Rome.[50][51]

events.description: World War II: In an event later dramatized in the movie The Great Escape, 76 Allied prisoners of war begin breaking out of the German camp Stalag Luft III.
events.html: • 1944 – World War II: In an event later dramatized in the movie The Great Escape, 76 Allied prisoners of war begin breaking out of the German camp Stalag Luft III.[52][53][54]

entities.name: German prisoner-of-war camps in World War II

events.description: A British Cabinet Mission arrives in India to discuss and plan for the transfer of power from the British Raj to Indian leadership.
events.html: • 1946 – A British Cabinet Mission arrives in India to discuss and plan for the transfer of power from the British Raj to Indian leadership.[55][56]

events.description: Hanns Albin Rauter, a chief SS and Police Leader, in the Netherlands, is convicted and executed for crimes against humanity.
events.html: • 1949 – Hanns Albin Rauter, a chief SS and Police Leader, in the Netherlands, is convicted and executed for crimes against humanity.[57]

events.description: The Quebec Board of the French Language is established.
events.html: • 1961 – The Quebec Board of the French Language is established.[58]

entities.name: Office québécois de la langue française

events.description: Direct rule is imposed on Northern Ireland by the Government of the United Kingdom under Edward Heath.
events.html: • 1972 – Direct rule is imposed on Northern Ireland by the Government of the United Kingdom under Edward Heath.[59]

events.description: In Argentina, the armed forces overthrow the constitutional government of President Isabel Perón and start a seven-year dictatorial period self-styled the National Reorganization Process.
events.html: • 1976 – In Argentina, the armed forces overthrow the constitutional government of President Isabel Perón and start a seven-year dictatorial period self-styled the National Reorganization Process.[60][61]

events.description: Morarji Desai became the Prime Minister of India, the first Prime Minister not to belong to Indian National Congress.
events.html: • 1977 – Morarji Desai became the Prime Minister of India, the first Prime Minister not to belong to Indian National Congress.[62][63]

events.description: El Salvadorian Archbishop Óscar Romero is assassinated while celebrating Mass in San Salvador.
events.html: • 1980 – El Salvadorian Archbishop Óscar Romero is assassinated while celebrating Mass in San Salvador.[64][65]

events.description: Bangladeshi President Abdus Sattar is deposed in a bloodless coup led by Army Chief Lieutenant general Hussain Muhammad Ershad, who suspends the Constitution and imposes martial law.
events.html: • 1982 – Bangladeshi President Abdus Sattar is deposed in a bloodless coup led by Army Chief Lieutenant general Hussain Muhammad Ershad, who suspends the Constitution and imposes martial law.[66]

events.description: The Loscoe gas explosion leads to new UK laws on landfill gas migration and gas protection on landfill sites.
events.html: • 1986 – The Loscoe gas explosion leads to new UK laws on landfill gas migration and gas protection on landfill sites.[67]

events.description: In Prince William Sound in Alaska, the Exxon Valdez spills 240,000 barrels (38,000 m3) of crude oil after running aground.
events.html: • 1989 – In Prince William Sound in Alaska, the Exxon Valdez spills 240,000 barrels (38,000 m3) of crude oil after running aground.[68][69]

events.description: Indian intervention in the Sri Lankan Civil War ends with last ship of Indian Peace Keeping Force leaving Sri Lanka.
events.html: • 1990 – Indian intervention in the Sri Lankan Civil War ends with last ship of Indian Peace Keeping Force leaving Sri Lanka.[70]

entities.name: Indian intervention in the Sri Lankan Civil War

events.description: Comet Shoemaker–Levy 9 is discovered by Carolyn and Eugene Shoemaker, and David Levy at the Palomar Observatory in California.
events.html: • 1993 – Comet Shoemaker–Levy 9 is discovered by Carolyn and Eugene Shoemaker, and David Levy at the Palomar Observatory in California.[71][72]

events.description: Mitchell Johnson and Andrew Golden, aged 11 and 13 respectively, open fire upon teachers and students at Westside Middle School in Jonesboro, Arkansas; five people are killed and ten are wounded.
events.html: • 1998 – Mitchell Johnson and Andrew Golden, aged 11 and 13 respectively, open fire upon teachers and students at Westside Middle School in Jonesboro, Arkansas; five people are killed and ten are wounded.[73][74]

events.description: A tornado sweeps through Dantan in India, killing 250 people and injuring 3,000 others.
events.html: • 1998 – A tornado sweeps through Dantan in India, killing 250 people and injuring 3,000 others.[75]

events.description: Dr. Rüdiger Marmulla performed the first computer-assisted Bone Segment Navigation at the University of Regensburg, Germany.
events.html: • 1998 – Dr. Rüdiger Marmulla performed the first computer-assisted Bone Segment Navigation at the University of Regensburg, Germany.[76][77]

events.description: Kosovo War: NATO began attacks on Yugoslavia without United Nations Security Council (UNSC) approval, marking the first time NATO has attacked a sovereign country.
events.html: • 1999 – Kosovo War: NATO began attacks on Yugoslavia without United Nations Security Council (UNSC) approval, marking the first time NATO has attacked a sovereign country.[78][79]

events.description: A lorry carrying margarine and flour catches fire inside the Mont Blanc Tunnel, creating an inferno that kills 38 people.
events.html: • 1999 – A lorry carrying margarine and flour catches fire inside the Mont Blanc Tunnel, creating an inferno that kills 38 people.[80]

events.description: The Arab League votes 21–1 in favor of a resolution demanding an end to the 2003 invasion of Iraq.
events.html: • 2003 – The Arab League votes 21–1 in favor of a resolution demanding an end to the 2003 invasion of Iraq.[81][82]

events.description: Bhutan officially becomes a democracy, with its first ever general election.
events.html: • 2008 – Bhutan officially becomes a democracy, with its first ever general election.[83]

events.description: Germanwings Flight 9525 crashes in the French Alps in an apparent pilot mass murder-suicide, killing all 150 people on board.
events.html: • 2015 – Germanwings Flight 9525 crashes in the French Alps in an apparent pilot mass murder-suicide, killing all 150 people on board.[84]

events.description: Syrian civil war: The Turkish Armed Forces (TAF) and Syrian National Army (SNA) take full control of Afrin District, marking the end of the Afrin offensive.
